(Corrects to say economy operating, not growing, below its
potential.)  Finance Minister  Jim Flaherty  said
the level of the Canadian economy is below its potential as the
country faces challenges such as Europe’s debt crisis.  Flaherty, speaking to reporters in Ottawa, said the global
economy remains “stubbornly fragile.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
